    # nfnetlink_subsys_unregister, nfnetlink_unicast, nla_reserve,
    # __nlmsg_put, skb_trim, nf_tables_trans_destroy_flush_work), and
    # netdev / rtnl glue for dummy.ko (dev_lstats_read, eth_mac_addr,
    # ethtool_op_get_ts_info, pernet_ops_rwsem DATA,
    # __rtnl_link_register, __rtnl_link_unregister,
    # skb_clone_tx_timestamp, skb_tstamp_tx). Total exports after L66:
    # 1287 + 23 = 1310 (under MAX_EXPORTS=2048).
    linux_abi_register_l66()

    # L67: xt_string.ko + xt_LED.ko + nft_chain_nat.ko + nft_masq.ko +
    # xt_MASQUERADE.ko. One ride-along module needs ZERO new exports
    # (xt_MASQUERADE.ko — every UND lands on the L<=66 surface plus
    # the four nf_nat_masquerade_* symbols shipped here for nft_masq).
    # The other four add 17 new symbols across four groups: textsearch
    # + skb scanning (textsearch_prepare, textsearch_destroy,
    # skb_find_text), LED-trigger core API (led_trigger_register,
    # led_trigger_unregister, led_trigger_event), nftables chain-type
    # registry + dispatcher (nft_register_chain_type,
    # nft_unregister_chain_type, nft_do_chain), and nf_nat per-family
    # register hooks + masquerade (nf_nat_inet_register_fn,
    # nf_nat_inet_unregister_fn, nf_nat_ipv6_register_fn,
    # nf_nat_ipv6_unregister_fn,
    # nf_nat_masquerade_inet_register_notifiers,
    # nf_nat_masquerade_inet_unregister_notifiers,
    # nf_nat_masquerade_ipv4, nf_nat_masquerade_ipv6). Total exports
    # after L67: 1310 + 17 = 1327 (under MAX_EXPORTS=2048).
    linux_abi_register_l67()

    # L68: xt_owner.ko + xt_REDIRECT.ko + nft_nat.ko + nft_quota.ko +
    # nft_limit.ko + xt_socket.ko. Three ride-along modules need ZERO
    # new exports (xt_owner.ko, xt_REDIRECT.ko, nft_nat.ko — every UND
    # already covered by L<=67). The other three add 6 new symbols
    # across two groups: nftables stateful-object registry + notify
    # (nft_register_obj, nft_unregister_obj, nft_obj_notify — consumed
    # by nft_quota.ko + nft_limit.ko) and netfilter socket lookup +
    # sock refcount put (nf_sk_lookup_slow_v4, nf_sk_lookup_slow_v6,
    # sock_gen_put — consumed by xt_socket.ko). Total exports after
    # L68: 1327 + 6 = 1333 (under MAX_EXPORTS=2048).
    linux_abi_register_l68()

    # e1000e pivot: 80 new exports to satisfy the stock Debian
    # e1000e.ko UND surface (the strategic pivot from hand-rolling
    # drivers/net/e1000e.ad to loading Linux's driver via the
    # L-series loader). Groups: ethtool/ptp/qos stubs, netdev_err
    # /vmalloc/ioremap/__kmalloc wrappers, PCI extensions
    # (pci_enable_device_mem / pci_select_bars / pcie_capability_*),
    # NAPI bookkeeping (netif_napi_add_weight, napi_enable/disable,
    # __napi_schedule, napi_complete_done, napi_gro_receive), sk_buff
    # gap-fillers (__dev_kfree_skb_*, __netdev_alloc_skb,
    # __napi_alloc_skb, ___pskb_trim, __skb_pad), timecounter trio,
    # and 4 DATA globals (current_task, softnet_data, __preempt_
    # count, param_array_ops). Full list: docs/e1000e_ko_gap.txt.
    # Total exports after this milestone: 1333 + 80 = 1413
    # (under MAX_EXPORTS=2048).
    linux_abi_register_e1000e()

    # Shared generic-shim owners hoisted out of per-NIC api_*.ad files
    # so any new driver that pulls libphy / MDIO / PCI-VPD / hwmon
    # symbols just resolves against these centralised owners (no
    # per-agent duplication). Registered AFTER api_e1000e — order
    # within the table doesn't change lookup semantics (linear scan,
    # first-match-wins), but keeping the NIC-specific shims earlier
    # preserves the historical layout. Counts:
    #   * phylib  : 38 phy_* / genphy_* (was: r8169 33 + tg3 5)
    #   * mdio    : 10 mdiobus_* (was: r8169 6 + tg3 4)
    #   * pci_vpd : 5 pci_vpd_* / pci_*_vpd_any (was: sky2 2 + tg3 3)
    #   * hwmon   : 4 hwmon_* / devm_hwmon_* (was: igb 1 + atlantic 1
    #                                            + tg3 2; merged into
    #                                            one stub buffer)
    # Total: 57 exports moved into shared owners.
    linux_abi_register_phylib()
    linux_abi_register_mdio()
    linux_abi_register_pci_vpd()
    linux_abi_register_hwmon()

    # Multi-NIC scale-out: r8169 (Realtek consumer GbE) — 70 new
    # exports beyond api_e1000e. Closes the PHY library + MDIO bus +
    # pcim_ devm + paged PHY register access surface so Linux's
    # stock r8169.ko loads + probes against QEMU's -device rtl8139
    # (whose PCI ID is in r8169's id_table for backward compat).
    linux_abi_register_r8169()

    # Multi-NIC scale-out: igb (Intel 82575/82576/82580/I210/I211/I350
    # server-class GbE) — 73 new exports beyond api_e1000e + api_r8169.
    # Closes the XDP / BPF / DCA / SR-IOV / i2c (SFP+) / flow-block
    # surface. Same insmod-success contract as r8169; the QEMU
    # `-device igb` line is the matching fixture when QEMU supports it.
    linux_abi_register_igb()

    # Storage pivot (Agent D): the 53 new exports the stock Debian
    # ahci.ko (Linux 6.1.0-32 build) needs beyond what L<=68 + e1000e
    # already exports. ahci.ko is the SATA AHCI controller driver
    # (covers ~80% of stock desktop/laptop SATA silicon: Intel ICH/PCH,
    # AMD SB/FCH, JMicron, Marvell, ASMedia). Categories: 10 ahci_*
    # entry points (libahci surface — host_activate, init_controller,
    # reset_controller, save_initial_config, ...), 23 ata_*/sata_*
    # (libata surface — host_alloc_pinfo, scsi_queuecmd, scsi_ioctl,
    # link_hardreset, scr_read, tf_to_fis, wait_after_reset, ...),
    # 7 pcim_*/pci_* (managed PCI + IRQ vector helpers — pcim_enable_
    # device, pcim_iomap_table, pci_alloc_irq_vectors_affinity,
    # pci_intx, pci_match_id), 4 dmi_* (no-DMI in our env), 2 misc
    # (devm_kmalloc, pm_suspend_default_s2idle), and 8 DATA exports
    # (ahci_ops, ahci_pmp_retry_srst_ops, ata_dummy_port_ops,
    # ahci_sdev_groups, ahci_shost_groups, ahci_ignore_sss,
    # sata_deb_timing_normal, sata_deb_timing_hotplug). Total exports
    # after ahci: 1413 + 53 = 1466.
    linux_abi_register_ahci()

    # Storage maximalism: scsi_mod.ko (SCSI mid-layer) + libata.ko
    # (ATA / SCSI translation). Bundling these two .ko files +
    # closing their UND surface unlocks the entire family of stock
    # Linux SCSI drivers (sd_mod, sr_mod, st_mod, mpt3sas,
    # megaraid_sas, qla2xxx, virtio_scsi, ...) — once scsi_mod +
    # libata load, any new SCSI driver only needs its silicon-
    # specific shim batch, NOT the full SCSI infrastructure.
    #
    # api_scsi.ad: ~96 exports (scsi_mod's 83 net-new UND symbols +
    # 13 shared-with-libata symbols owned here because scsi_mod
    # loads first via modules.dep). Categories: 37 blk_*/blk_mq_*/
    # blk_queue_* extensions beyond api_block + api_nvme, 6 sg_*/
    # scsi_* primitives (scatter-gather + sense-buffer parsing),
    # 7 sbitmap_*/ida_* (bit + ID allocators), 9 transport_*/
    # attribute_container_*, 4 trace_seq_*/trace_print_hex_seq,
    # ~28 misc (devm/sysfs/jiffies/etc), 5 DATA exports
    # (scsi_command_size_tbl, scsi_device_type, platform_bus,
    # system_long_wq, param_ops_string).
    #
    # api_libata.ad: ~43 exports (libata's net-new UND symbols).
    # Categories: 5 acpi_*, 7 devres_/devm_, 9 ioread*/iowrite*,
    # 2 scsi_set_sense_*, 3 sg_miter_*, 12 misc (async/blk_abort/
    # glob_match/strcasecmp/strim/kstrtoll/ledtrig/wake), 1 DATA
    # export (acpi_gbl_FADT).
    #
    # Loader ordering: modules.dep auto-loads scsi_mod -> libata
    # -> libahci -> ahci, which means the api_ahci.ad stubs for
    # ata_* / sata_* / ahci_* are SUPERSEDED at runtime by libata's
    # real EXPORT_SYMBOL surface via the loader's cross-module
    # ksymtab fallback (loader-unify commit deb21cc). The shims
    # below are the floor; libata's real implementations win when
    # libata is loaded.
    #
    # Total exports added by this batch: 96 + 43 = 139.
    linux_abi_register_scsi()
    linux_abi_register_libata()

    # Storage pivot (Agent D): the 89 new exports the stock Debian
    # nvme.ko (Linux 6.1.0-32 build) needs beyond what L<=68 + e1000e
    # + ahci already exports. nvme.ko is the PCIe NVM Express SSD
    # driver — every modern (post-2014) NVMe SSD speaks this protocol.
    # Unlike ahci/libata, nvme bypasses the SCSI mid-layer entirely
    # and talks directly to blk-mq, giving a leaner UND surface.
    # Categories: 37 nvme_* / __nvme_* (nvme-core substitutes —
    # init_ctrl, init_ctrl_finish, start_ctrl, reset_ctrl, change_
    # ctrl_state, disable_ctrl/enable_ctrl/shutdown_ctrl, set/get_
    # features, complete_rq, setup/cleanup_cmd, submit_sync_cmd,
    # start/stop_admin_queue, start/stop_queues, freeze/unfreeze,
    # cancel_tagset, remove_namespaces, sec_submit), 14 blk_mq_*
    # extensions (alloc_request, free_request, init_queue, destroy_
    # queue, start_request, map_queues, pci_map_queues, update_nr_
    # hw_queues, complete_request_remote, end_request_batch,
    # execute_rq_nowait, get/put_queue, __blk_rq_map_sg), 8 pci_*/
    # pcibios_*/pcie_aspm_* (request_irq, free_irq, request_selected_
    # regions, load_saved_state, device_is_present, pcibios_resource_
    # to_bus, sriov_configure_simple, aspm_enabled), 6 mempool_*
    # (create_node, destroy, alloc, free, kmalloc, kfree), 3 opal_*
    # (init/free_opal_dev, opal_unlock_from_suspend), 16 misc
    # (async_schedule_node — invoked synchronously; wait_for_completion_
    # io_timeout, dma_map_sgtable, dma_max_mapping_size, dma_pci_
    # p2pdma_supported, __kmalloc_node, kmalloc_node_trace, dmi_match,
    # __flush_workqueue, param_set_uint_minmax, __do_once_start/_done,
    # __bitmap_weight, dma_unmap_sg_attrs, device_release_driver,
    # disable_irq), and 9 DATA exports (admin_timeout, nvme_io_timeout,
    # nvme_wq, nvme_dev_attrs_group, acpi_storage_d3, cpu_number,
    # __SCK__tp_func_nvme_sq, __SCT__tp_func_nvme_sq,
    # __tracepoint_nvme_sq). Total exports after nvme: 1466 + 89 = 1555.
    linux_abi_register_nvme()

    # NVMe-core side-load closure: 102 net-new exports for the
    # stock nvme-core.ko (Debian 6.1.0-32 build, ~380 KiB). The
    # binary is loaded via the L-shim as nvme.ko's `depends:
    # nvme-core` dep — see init/main.ad's [boot:35.N] path which
    # uses modules_dep_load_with_deps("nvme", 4) to walk the chain.
    # Once nvme-core.ko is loaded, the loader's ksymtab fallback
    # (commit deb21cc) resolves nvme.ko's nvme_*/__SCK_*/__SCT_*/
    # tracepoint relocations against nvme-core's REAL EXPORT_SYMBOL
    # impls — visible as `[ksymtab_hit] nvme -> nvme_core: <symbol>`
    # for the 45-symbol overlap with api_nvme.ad's cold-path stubs.
    # The result: nvme_submit_sync_cmd is the real Linux body, not
    # the -ENODEV stub; namespace scan + IDENTIFY can flow.
    #
    # Categories: 38 blk_*/blk_mq_*/blk_queue_*, 6 bio_* + submit_
    # bio_noacct, 5 srcu_*, 2 xa_* (xa_store, xa_find_after), 3
    # io_uring_cmd_*, 12 gendisk/device-add-disk family (add_disk,
    # __blk_alloc_disk, __blk_mq_alloc_disk, put_disk, bdev_disk_
    # changed, blk_revalidate_disk_zones, disk_set_zoned, disk_
    # uevent, disk_update_readahead, set_capacity_and_notify,
    # set_disk_ro, blk_integrity_register/unregister, blk_mark_disk_
    # dead), 2 cdev_device_*, 4 PM-QoS + hwmon, 11 misc helpers
    # (ida_alloc/destroy/free, kfree_const, __node_distance,
    # kblockd_schedule_work, sed_ioctl, device_remove_file_self,
    # trace_seq_printf/putc, sysfs_streq), 4 PI/CRC helpers
    # (t10_pi_type1/3_crc, ext_pi_type1/3_crc64), 9 DATA exports
    # (uuid_null, node_states, param_ops_byte, __SCK__/__SCT__/
    # __tracepoint__ for block_bio_complete + block_bio_remap).
    # Total exports after nvme_core: 1555 + 102 = 1657.
    #
    # 24 names overlap with the SCSI mid-layer agent's api_scsi.ad
    # / api_libata.ad — first-match-wins on linux_abi_lookup, so
    # whichever registers first owns the lookup. Cold-path semantics
    # are equivalent (all return BLK_STS_OK / no-op / -EINVAL).
    linux_abi_register_nvme_core()

    # USB host-controller scale-out: usbcore + xhci_pci + xhci_hcd +
    # ehci_pci + ehci_hcd. Loads via the L-shim; matched by the
    # auto-modules path on PCI class 0x0C0330 (xhci) and 0x0C0320
    # (ehci). usbcore.ko had 9 new UND symbols beyond L<=68 (sysfs
    # bin-files, __get_free_pages, kmemdup, tasklet runtime, list
    # validator). xhci_pci.ko had 29 new UND (xhci-hcd cross-module
    # like xhci_init_driver / xhci_gen_setup / xhci_suspend /
    # xhci_resume / xhci_shutdown / xhci_dbg_trace / xhci_ext_cap_init
    # / xhci_update_hub_device, the three xhci_dbg_quirks tracepoint
    # statics, the pci_choose_state / pci_d3cold_disable / pci_match_id
    # / pci_set_mwi / pm_suspend_target_state / __devm_reset_control_get
    # / reset_control_reset PCI extensions, the Intel/AMD quirks).
    # ehci_pci.ko had 7 new UND beyond xhci's batch (ehci_init_driver /
    # ehci_setup / ehci_suspend / ehci_resume, pci_clear_mwi /
    # pci_find_capability, usb_amd_hang_symptom_quirk). xhci_hcd.ko's
    # 5 gap symbols + ehci_hcd.ko's 2 gap symbols (devm_add_action,
    # __kmalloc_node, kmalloc_node_trace, __list_del_entry_valid,
    # usb_hcd_irq, strlcat) are covered through the same usbcore +
    # xhci + ehci shim wiring above (each name appears once in the
    # union of the three new files).
    # Cross-module symbol resolution (xhci_pci references symbols
    # DEFINED in xhci_hcd / usbcore; ehci_pci references symbols
    # DEFINED in ehci_hcd / usbcore): we ship all of them as Hamnix
    # shims so the auto-loader doesn't need modules.dep load-order
    # sequencing. modules.dep parsing is a follow-up.
    # Five tail symbols (usb_hcd_irq for xhci/ehci hcd's request_irq,
    # devm_add_action / __kmalloc_node / kmalloc_node_trace for the
    # NUMA-aware slab paths, strlcat for ehci_hcd's name builder) get
    # tucked into api_usbcore.ad because that's the natural owner.
    # Total exports after this milestone: 1556 + ~42 = ~1598.
    linux_abi_register_usbcore()
    linux_abi_register_xhci()
    linux_abi_register_ehci()
    # USB host-controller (struct usb_hcd / struct hc_driver) shim
    # layer. Registered AFTER usbcore so it OVERWRITES the cold stubs
    # for usb_create_hcd / usb_create_shared_hcd / usb_add_hcd /
    # usb_hcd_pci_probe / usb_hcd_irq / usb_hcd_is_primary_hcd with
    # the real-bridged implementations in api_usb_hcd.ad. With this
    # in place the PCI walker no longer needs to SKIP USB-HC class
    # devices — the .ko's xhci_pci_probe now runs end-to-end and
    # the L-shim bridges into drivers/usb/xhci.ad::xhci_init() for
    # the real MMIO controller bring-up.
    linux_abi_register_usb_hcd()

    # HID-class L-shim: hid.ko (HID core library, ~480 KiB) +
    # usbhid.ko (USB HID transport, ~180 KiB). Together they close
    # the load-time symbol gap for the
    # `usbhid + hid + usbcore + xhci_hcd + xhci_pci` dep chain.
    # api_hid.ad ships 17 new UND shims for hid.ko's gap and exports
    # the cross-module hid_* surface usbhid.ko UND-references;
    # api_usbhid.ad ships 49 new UND shims for usbhid.ko's gap
    # (URB lifecycle + control_msg + autopm + driver-registration).
    # The actual keystroke data path is unchanged from the previous
    # milestone — drivers/usb/xhci.ad::xhci_poll → hid_kbd_report
    # → kbd_rx_push delivers real keyboard events. The .ko loads
    # are a Linux-ABI coverage probe that proves the dep chain
    # resolves without symbol gaps.
    linux_abi_register_hid()
    linux_abi_register_usbhid()

    # Audio scale-out: Intel HD Audio family — snd_hda_intel.ko +
    # snd.ko + snd_pcm.ko + snd_hda_core.ko + snd_hda_codec.ko. Same
    # V0 strategy as the NIC family — shim every cross-.ko reference
    # on the Hamnix side so modules.dep ordering isn't required.
    linux_abi_register_snd_core()
    linux_abi_register_snd_pcm()
    linux_abi_register_snd_hda()

    # WiFi pivot: cfg80211 + mac80211 — foundational framework
    # modules every wifi driver depends on. No PCI alias of their
    # own — loaded explicitly by init/main.ad via the
    # /etc/framework-modules marker BEFORE the auto-load PCI walk.
    linux_abi_register_cfg80211()
    linux_abi_register_mac80211()

    # Multi-NIC scale-out (round 2): atlantic (Aquantia 10G), alx
    # (Qualcomm Atheros), sky2 (Marvell Yukon 2), tg3 (Broadcom
    # NetXtreme). Each .ko load is a coverage probe of the remaining
    # shim gap. Per-driver UND/missing tallies (against
    # L<=68 + api_e1000e + api_r8169 + api_igb):
    #
    #     alx       :   4 new exports
    #     atlantic  :  16 new exports
    #     sky2      :   6 new exports
    #     tg3       :  26 new exports
    #
    # Ordering matters because shared symbols (dev_kfree_skb_any_reason,
    # __dma_sync_single_for_{cpu,device}, pci_ioremap_bar,
    # __kmalloc_large_noprof, __alloc_pages_noprof) appear in multiple
    # drivers' UND lists but only need a single _add_export(). The
    # ownership table:
    #   * alx owns dev_kfree_skb_any_reason (also needed by atlantic,
    #     sky2, tg3) and pci_ioremap_bar (also tg3).
    #   * atlantic owns __dma_sync_single_for_cpu (also tg3),
    #     __alloc_pages_noprof + __kmalloc_large_noprof (also tg3).
    #   * sky2 owns __dma_sync_single_for_device (also tg3).
    # Total exports added by this batch: 4 + 16 + 6 + 26 = 52.
    linux_abi_register_alx()
    linux_abi_register_atlantic()
    linux_abi_register_sky2()
    linux_abi_register_tg3()

    # Autostub safety net (scripts/gen_autostubs.py). Called LAST so
    # hand-rolled shims always win the linear-scan lookup; autostub
    # entries only fire for symbols the hand-shims missed.
    linux_abi_register_autostubs()

    # MAX_EXPORTS overflow guard: the wifi bug (d77e7e3) was a silent
    # overflow that hid for two days. Warn at boot if we hit the cap.
    if NR_EXPORTS >= MAX_EXPORTS:
        printk0("linux_abi: WARN: NR_EXPORTS == MAX_EXPORTS at boot; bump MAX_EXPORTS in linux_abi/exports.ad\n")


def linux_abi_lookup(name: Ptr[char]) -> uint64:
    # Linear scan, LAST-MATCH wins. Returns the kernel address for
    # `name`, or 0 if not found (loader treats that as "unresolved
    # external" and logs a diagnostic).
    #
    # Last-match semantics: when two batches register the same name
    # (e.g. api_ahci.ad and api_usb_hcd.ad both stubbing pci_match_id),
    # the LATER registration wins. This matches how Linux's
    # EXPORT_SYMBOL resolution behaves when a later-loaded module
    # provides an overriding implementation — and it lets a focused
    # follow-up file (api_usb_hcd.ad in 2026-05) repair an earlier
    # batch's shortcut without editing the original file.
    #
    # Concrete case the change unblocks: api_ahci.ad's
    # _ahc_pci_match_id returns the FIRST entry of the id table
    # unconditionally (a safe shortcut for ahci's id_table whose
    # first entry is the "generic AHCI" fallback). When xhci_pci.ko's
    # xhci_pci_quirks calls pci_match_id with its xhci-specific quirks
    # table, that "return first entry" semantics returns a non-NULL
    # pointer whose driver_data is then dereferenced — and ends up
    # reading garbage memory because the quirks table's first entry
    # is just an empty terminator. With last-match wins, api_usb_hcd.ad
    # re-registers pci_match_id with a no-quirk-found (NULL) impl that
    # the xhci_pci_quirks codepath handles correctly.
    i: uint64 = NR_EXPORTS
    while i > 0:
        i = i - 1
        nm: Ptr[uint8] = cast[Ptr[uint8]](export_names[i])
        if _streq(nm, cast[Ptr[uint8]](name)) == 1:
            return export_addrs[i]
    return 0
